  ('best_practice', 'Break up PDP copy with small feature-callout banners that translate specs into benefits', 'High-converting product pages (Growth.design''s Apple/Tesla-style teardowns) don''t dump a wall of specifications — they intersperse small, focused feature-callout banners, each pairing one technical feature with the concrete benefit it delivers and a subtle supporting visual or micro-animation that reveals on scroll. These mid-page banners do three jobs: they break the monotony of body copy (so users keep reading), they convert abstract specs into reasons to buy, and they apply gentle persuasion principles — one idea per block (chunking), a visual that demonstrates rather than tells, and motion that draws the eye without nagging. Keep each callout to a single feature→benefit pairing; stacking many claims into one banner dilutes all of them. Use animation sparingly and never as the only way the information is conveyed (respect reduced-motion).', '{"applicable_when":"mid-PDP section banners between long-form product description blocks","category":"pdp","evidence_source":"Growth.design case studies (growth.design/case-studies) — Apple/Tesla-style feature sections, applied behavioral psychology"}'::jsonb, '[0.0071116337,-0.003385688,0.011352205,-0.087250866,0.014535028,-0.009882196,0.0069199,-0.0010217661,0.0022770837,-0.012474693,-0.022595499,0.0152970115,0.021607019,-0.004409885,0.099673316,0.035159387,0.038482662,-0.024617432,0.020433469,-0.0051532495,-0.003069866,-0.0038089927,-0.029038778,-0.013837266,0.0032622807,-0.034522884,0.023545455,0.013365326,0.038145956,0.024992224,-0.0067314412,0.023555644,0.031038245,0.022896754,0.032223552,0.012115889,0.021309728,-0.009649118,0.0039588874,0.029241145,0.0058266,-0.0007396152,0.020552022,0.0037931777,-0.033761874,-0.016183272,0.015478921,-0.008024282,-0.00097351783,0.03653456,-0.02619492,0.016555114,0.015674401,-0.17294694,0.0024319473,0.009175068,0.011532637,0.0008782229,0.008962504,-0.010064743,-0.016389117,0