  ('best_practice', 'Clinical beauty brands should lead with ingredient specificity and proof of mechanism over lifestyle imagery', 'Drunk Elephant''s hero copy names the mechanism: "skin-smart formulas developed with efficacious levels of active ingredients that can be easily absorbed and put to use." The Ordinary uses "CLINICAL WITH INTEGRITY" as a positioning headline. These brands do not use lifestyle imagery or aspirational language — they use specificity and transparency. For clinical brands, the banner body copy should reference an ingredient, clinical outcome, or formulation principle rather than a generic beauty benefit. Avoid phrases like "best skin ever" or "radiant glow" in clinical brand contexts — they read as category noise rather than brand signal.', '{"applicable_when":"clinical, dermatology, and science-led beauty brand banners","category":"brand","evidence_source":"Drive corpus — Drunk Elephant ''efficacious levels of active ingredients'', The Ordinary ''CLINICAL WITH INTEGRITY'' 2026-05"}'::jsonb, '[-0.0076015973,-0.0038827865,-0.013761762,-0.075664975,-0.012133571,-0.0015605188,-0.010345199,-0.011091947,0.0014867648,-0.017401513,-0.01343577,0.010330701,0.018548246,-0.011189126,0.109102994,0.015211872,-0.013508944,0.012940858,0.014914769,0.00503952,0.007355103,0.011411766,-0.0068980446,-0.015009791,-0.0072127944,-0.0035042793,-0.015108872,0.020045612,0.026078563,0.010056553,-0.017376447,-0.002951774,0.049063608,0.013484489,0.0006806356,0.025632735,0.023425372,-0.02829451,0.0151467705,0.022415932,-0.0098823495,0.036381047,0.0099082915,-0.0078046336,-0.0035570767,0.0001224691,0.01799095,-0.015165301,0.0054737786,0.0222384,-0.005411348,0.01532635,-0.018732265,-0.15622056,0.0013729485,-0.0014398878,0.016012298,-0.011977438,-0.005523333,-0.014515178,-0.019929826,0.009136906,-0.015612934,-0.039469365,0.00033088902,-0.044094443,-0.0077582314,-0.02411828,0.009712964,0.0076330197,0.0071893474,-0.0012266008,-0.025033176,0.0075299027,-0.0010617028,-0.019059