  ('best_practice', 'Fitts''s Law — make the primary CTA big and close; time-to-target depends on target size and distance', 'Fitts''s Law: the time to acquire a target is a function of its size and the distance to it — big targets are easier and faster to hit, and small controls crammed together cause mis-taps. Apply it by making the primary CTA prominently sized and comfortable to activate, placing it close to where the user''s attention/finger already is (e.g. directly after the headline flow), and giving secondary actions adequate spacing so they''re not fat-fingered by mistake. On touch this reinforces the 44px minimum tap-target rule and argues against tiny, tightly-packed links inside a banner. Usability here is motor-ergonomic, not just visual: a beautifully styled but small or awkwardly-placed CTA still costs clicks. (Pairs with [mobile_tap_target_44px], [cta_button_contrast].)', '{"applicable_when":"sizing and placing CTA buttons and tap targets in any banner","category":"ux_law","evidence_source":"Hype4 Academy / SquarePlanet — Laws of UX: Fitts''s Law (hype4.academy/learn/laws-of-ux/fitts)"}'::jsonb, '[0.004157521,-0.02193416,0.017583128,-0.086373284,-0.004476854,-0.0034886429,-0.016138181,-0.0039397925,0.014151725,0.00323655,-0.02105423,0.02498007,-0.0029802946,-0.01712881,0.12820463,0.02270616,-0.006804503,-0.033825394,-0.01219752,0.010872918,-0.011716545,0.022812042,-0.02915171,-0.015424007,0.009870159,-0.023908766,0.043410122,0.006587298,0.02053668,0.03377351,-0.032621104,0.005047716,0.023713354,0.012591585,-0.013506869,0.021199983,0.011182129,-0.0296081,0.010813997,0.02847182,0.009079755,-0.013359057,0.019216895,0.0296948,-0.03126981,0.0026021134,0.0032641909,-0.018446857,-0.013027248,0.046901096,-0.012769746,0.020304859,-0.01591961,-0.15883821,0.0125717,-0.0007609469,-0.0049447203,0.029458513,-0.009942516,0.024149353,0.0057406845,0.03789165,0.0106415795,-0.036725156,-0.012544622,-0.02444642,-0.0020358635,0.0054762205,-0.015961247,0.009787309,0.0002