  ('best_practice', 'Lead the headline with the consumer benefit, not the product category', 'Benefit-led headlines like "Glow Beyond Beauty" and "The Drunk Difference" outperform category-first headlines like "Skincare Products" by anchoring the consumer on the outcome, not the SKU. The supporting line should name the product or mechanism: "skin-smart formulas developed with efficacious levels of active ingredients." For promotional banners, the benefit is the discount outcome — "radiant, silky-smooth results" — not the offer mechanic. Drunk Elephant and Bearen both place product names only in secondary positions after the benefit hook is established.', '{"applicable_when":"hero banners, brand awareness campaigns","category":"hierarchy","evidence_source":"Drive corpus — Drunk Elephant ''The Drunk Difference'', Bearen ''Glow Beyond Beauty'' 2026-05"}'::jsonb, '[-0.0180429,0.013002136,0.0040110797,-0.08322847,-0.014685483,0.0120599205,-0.0017687363,0.0053381943,0.0072324206,0.009286037,-0.00931015,-0.0029294852,0.010915954,-0.0124427155,0.09791113,0.011638188,0.026698463,-0.0041195042,0.016355356,-0.003417204,0.007084419,0.021555541,-0.0050109243,-0.017685981,0.005778027,0.0018382062,0.016871206,0.010838862,0.014788949,0.0022695,-0.002305464,0.010540982,0.02916396,0.009619079,0.018517766,0.038781088,0.037716843,-0.030928448,0.0011918646,0.01838922,0.0061096726,0.01177807,0.011394599,-0.00024924087,0.004939275,0.005632325,0.004223723,-0.01393222,0.010442266,0.01702741,-0.00810378,0.033993877,-0.01287428,-0.15197346,-0.0022507256,-0.016759528,-0.0027228794,-0.021538917,0.004568607,-0.008420733,-0.014214171,0.006808708,-0.02492655,-0.062598504,0.012028221,-0.03910959,0.002276536,-0.027632764,0.0019840049,0.016764998,0.0076064845,-0.000827827,-0.007116331,-0.002330554,0.019746277,-0.004085003,0.011552414,-0.010746342,-0.002027184,-0.017252995,0.0079167215,0.0049652327,-0.04781904,-0.004142106,-0.0038357037,0.012901585,-0.038768973,0.002283745,0.0045475313,0.001799034,0.0