  ('best_practice', 'Validate section banners with scroll/click heatmaps — watch for false bottoms and friction, not just clicks', 'A mid-page section banner can act as a positive visual stop or as a wall that ends the session — heatmaps tell you which. Read three maps together: a scroll map shows the average fold and the % of users reaching 25/50/75% depth, exposing a "false bottom" where a banner''s large whitespace or hard divider makes users think the page has ended and they stop scrolling; a click/tap map shows whether the banner''s CTA actually gets engaged; and a move/rage-click map flags friction — dense cursor movement with no clicks (confusion about what''s interactive) or repeated rage-clicks. If a scroll map shows users dropping off before reaching key content below a banner, either move that content up or strengthen the reason to continue past the banner. Judge a section banner by whether traffic flows *through* it (continued scroll + CTA clicks), not merely by impressions — a banner everyone scrolls past, or stops at, is failing regardless of how it looks.', '{"applicable_when":"post-launch evaluation of mid-page section banners","category":"measurement","evidence_source":"Hotjar — heatmaps guide & scroll maps (hotjar.com/heatmaps/examples, hotjar.com/blog/scroll-maps)"}'::jsonb, '[0.010042205,-0.0038523474,0.0041375984,-0.08375931,-0.011554134,0.010847591,-0.0028979836,-0.0045737405,-0.0045800363,-0.015872244,0.012374037,0.007918154,0.0144607695,0.009524734,0.102498285,0.012947212,0.0123910345,-0.01934029,0.014256256,-0.0071786284,0.01460925,0.018365737,-0.023424758,-0.031795144,-0.00038911102,-0.02530121,0.008893568,0.012974266,0.041922674,0.009231827,-0.034629084,0.003710019,0.040133916,-0.0023053633,0.0017311005,0.031812575,0.004756874,-0.0025681395,0.0072422917,0.02820233,0.00031139198,0.01739909,0.018835986,0.0011277924,-0.028641324,-0.014492839,5.4372544e-05,-0.0202705,0.0034124863,0.052561987,-0.015976058,0.03946677,0.01204101,-0.17938662,-0.00